
@startuml

class Student {
  +id: String
  +name: String
  +email: String
  +coursesRegistered: List<Course>
  +requestAppointment(course: Course, date: Date, time: Time)
}

class TeachingAssistant {
  +id: String
  +name: String
  +email: String
  +coursesTaught: List<Course>
  +acceptAppointment(appointment: Appointment)
}

class Course {
  +id: String
  +title: String
  +description: String
  +studentsRegistered: List<Student>
  +teachingAssistants: List<TeachingAssistant>
}

class Appointment {
  +id: String
  +date: Date
  +time: Time
  +course: Course
  +ta: TeachingAssistant
  +student: Student
  +status: String
}

Student "1" -- "0..*" Course : registeredFor
TeachingAssistant "1" -- "0..*" Course : teaches
Course "1" -- "1" Appointment : has
Appointment "1" -- "1" Student : for
Appointment "1" -- "1" TeachingAssistant : with

@enduml

### Explanation of Relationships:

- **Student** can register for multiple **Courses**.
- **TeachingAssistant** can teach multiple **Courses**.
- Each **Appointment** is associated with exactly one **Course**, one **TeachingAssistant**, and one **Student**.
- A **Student** can only request an appointment for a **Course** they are registered in.
- A **TeachingAssistant** can only provide help for the **Courses** they are teaching.

